<h2> JavaScript can change HTML attrbute values. </h2>
<h3>On Button click change the src value of the  image tag</h3>

<button onclick="document.getElementById('myImage').src='https://cdn4.vectorstock.com/i/1000x1000/48/08/realistic-glowing-light-bulb-on-dark-background-vector-3374808.jpg'">
Turn on the bulb</button>

<img id="myImage" src="https://secure.i.telegraph.co.uk/multimedia/archive/03055/philips-clear-led-_3055499b.jpg" style="width:100px">

<button onclick="document.getElementById('myImage').src='https://secure.i.telegraph.co.uk/multimedia/archive/03055/philips-clear-led-_3055499b.jpg'">
Turn off the bulb</button>


</body>
</html>
